{
  "video_id": "GqGksNRYu8s",
  "title": "We've stopped trusting institutions and started trusting strangers | Rachel Botsman",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 12760.0,
      "end_time": 15320.0,
      "text": "Let&#39;s talk about trust."
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 16239.0,
      "end_time": 19735.0,
      "text": "We all know trust is fundamental,"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 19760.0,
      "end_time": 22376.0,
      "text": "but when it comes to trusting people,"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 22400.0,
      "end_time": 25159.0,
      "text": "something profound is happening."
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 25800.0,
      "end_time": 27560.0,
      "text": "Please raise your hand"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 27800.0,
      "end_time": 31400.0,
      "text": "if you have ever been a host or a guest on Airbnb."
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 32400.0,
      "end_time": 35616.0,
      "text": "Wow. That&#39;s a lot of you."
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 35640.0,
      "end_time": 37800.0,
      "text": "Who owns Bitcoin?"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 38640.0,
      "end_time": 39896.0,
      "text": "Still a lot of you. OK."
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 39920.0,
      "end_time": 42616.0,
      "text": "And please raise your hand if you&#39;ve ever used Tinder"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 42640.0,
      "end_time": 44256.0,
      "text": "to help you find a mate."
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 44280.0,
      "end_time": 46960.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 46120.0,
      "end_time": 49495.0,
      "text": "This one&#39;s really hard to count because you&#39;re kind of going like this."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 49520.0,
      "end_time": 51336.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 51360.0,
      "end_time": 54135.0,
      "text": "These are all examples of how technology"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 54160.0,
      "end_time": 56256.0,
      "text": "is creating new mechanisms"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 56280.0,
      "end_time": 62296.0,
      "text": "that are enabling us to trust unknown people, companies and ideas."
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 62320.0,
      "end_time": 64336.0,
      "text": "And yet at the same time,"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 64360.0,
      "end_time": 65896.0,
      "text": "trust in institutions --"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 65920.0,
      "end_time": 68856.0,
      "text": "banks, governments and even churches --"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 68880.0,
      "end_time": 70256.0,
      "text": "is collapsing."
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 70280.0,
      "end_time": 72496.0,
      "text": "So what&#39;s happening here,"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 72520.0,
      "end_time": 74280.0,
      "text": "and who do you trust?"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 74800.0,
      "end_time": 78696.0,
      "text": "Let&#39;s start in France with a platform -- with a company, I should say --"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 78720.0,
      "end_time": 80856.0,
      "text": "with a rather funny-sounding name,"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 80880.0,
      "end_time": 82136.0,
      "text": "BlaBlaCar."
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 82160.0,
      "end_time": 85776.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s a platform that matches drivers and passengers"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 85800.0,
      "end_time": 89816.0,
      "text": "who want to share long-distance journeys together."
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 89840.0,
      "end_time": 94560.0,
      "text": "The average ride taken is 320 kilometers."
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 94800.0,
      "end_time": 98679.0,
      "text": "So it&#39;s a good idea to choose your fellow travelers wisely."
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 99320.0,
      "end_time": 103295.0,
      "text": "Social profiles and reviews help people make a choice."
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 103320.0,
      "end_time": 108336.0,
      "text": "You can see if someone&#39;s a smoker, you can see what kind of music they like,"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 108360.0,
      "end_time": 111960.0,
      "text": "you can see if they&#39;re going to bring their dog along for the ride."
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 112440.0,
      "end_time": 116150.0,
      "text": "But it turns out that the key social identifier"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 116400.0,
      "end_time": 118656.0,
      "text": "is how much you&#39;re going to talk in the car."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 118680.0,
      "end_time": 120496.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 120520.0,
      "end_time": 122136.0,
      "text": "Bla, not a lot,"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 122160.0,
      "end_time": 124456.0,
      "text": "bla bla, you want a nice bit of chitchat,"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 124480.0,
      "end_time": 128216.0,
      "text": "and bla bla bla, you&#39;re not going to stop talking the entire way"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 128240.00000000001,
      "end_time": 129696.00000000001,
      "text": "from London to Paris."
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 129720.0,
      "end_time": 132160.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 132400.0,
      "end_time": 135550.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s remarkable, right, that this idea works at all,"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 135800.0,
      "end_time": 138936.0,
      "text": "because it&#39;s counter to the lesson most of us were taught as a child:"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 138960.0,
      "end_time": 141280.0,
      "text": "never get in a car with a stranger."
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 141680.0,
      "end_time": 146816.0,
      "text": "And yet, BlaBlaCar transports more than four million people"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 146840.0,
      "end_time": 148800.0,
      "text": "every single month."
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 148880.0,
      "end_time": 151216.0,
      "text": "To put that in context, that&#39;s more passengers"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 151240.0,
      "end_time": 154720.0,
      "text": "than the Eurostar or JetBlue airlines carry."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 155360.0,
      "end_time": 159496.0,
      "text": "BlaBlaCar is a beautiful illustration of how technology is enabling"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 159520.0,
      "end_time": 163120.0,
      "text": "millions of people across the world to take a trust leap."
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 163560.0,
      "end_time": 169816.0,
      "text": "A trust leap happens when we take the risk to do something new or different"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 169840.0,
      "end_time": 171880.0,
      "text": "to the way that we&#39;ve always done it."
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 172440.0,
      "end_time": 175000.0,
      "text": "Let&#39;s try to visualize this together."
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 175360.0,
      "end_time": 178520.0,
      "text": "OK. I want you to close your eyes."
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 179320.0,
      "end_time": 182376.0,
      "text": "There is a man staring at me with his eyes wide open."
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 182400.0,
      "end_time": 184856.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m on this big red circle. I can see."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 184880.0,
      "end_time": 186296.0,
      "text": "So close your eyes."
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 186320.0,
      "end_time": 189176.0,
      "text": "(Laughter) (Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 189200.0,
      "end_time": 190456.0,
      "text": "I&#39;ll do it with you."
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 190480.0,
      "end_time": 193495.0,
      "text": "And I want you to imagine there exists a gap"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 193520.0,
      "end_time": 196800.0,
      "text": "between you and something unknown."
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 196760.0,
      "end_time": 199616.0,
      "text": "That unknown can be someone you&#39;ve just met."
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 199640.0,
      "end_time": 201736.0,
      "text": "It can be a place you&#39;ve never been to."
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 201760.0,
      "end_time": 205136.0,
      "text": "It can be something you&#39;ve never tried before."
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 205160.0,
      "end_time": 206376.0,
      "text": "You got it?"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 206400.0,
      "end_time": 208496.0,
      "text": "OK. You can open your eyes now."
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 208520.0,
      "end_time": 211856.0,
      "text": "For you to leap from a place of certainty,"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 211880.0,
      "end_time": 215456.0,
      "text": "to take a chance on that someone or something unknown,"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 215480.0,
      "end_time": 218816.0,
      "text": "you need a force to pull you over the gap,"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 218840.0,
      "end_time": 221680.0,
      "text": "and that remarkable force is trust."
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 222560.0,
      "end_time": 226176.0,
      "text": "Trust is an elusive concept,"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 226200.0,
      "end_time": 229576.0,
      "text": "and yet we depend on it for our lives to function."
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 229600.0,
      "end_time": 231856.0,
      "text": "I trust my children"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 231880.0,
      "end_time": 234736.0,
      "text": "when they say they&#39;re going to turn the lights out at night."
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 234760.0,
      "end_time": 237976.0,
      "text": "I trusted the pilot who flew me here to keep me safe."
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 238000.0,
      "end_time": 240816.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s a word we use a lot,"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 240840.0,
      "end_time": 243256.0,
      "text": "without always thinking about what it really means"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 243280.0,
      "end_time": 246656.0,
      "text": "and how it works in different contexts of our lives."
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 246680.0,
      "end_time": 250296.0,
      "text": "There are, in fact, hundreds of definitions of trust,"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 250320.0,
      "end_time": 254896.0,
      "text": "and most can be reduced to some kind of risk assessment"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 254920.0,
      "end_time": 257680.0,
      "text": "of how likely it is that things will go right."
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 258120.0,
      "end_time": 260696.0,
      "text": "But I don&#39;t like this definition of trust,"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 260720.00000000003,
      "end_time": 265160.0,
      "text": "because it makes trust sound rational and predictable,"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 265400.0,
      "end_time": 267616.0,
      "text": "and it doesn&#39;t really get to the human essence"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 267640.0,
      "end_time": 269575.0,
      "text": "of what it enables us to do"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 269600.0,
      "end_time": 271576.0,
      "text": "and how it empowers us"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 271600.0,
      "end_time": 273696.0,
      "text": "to connect with other people."
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 273720.0,
      "end_time": 275776.0,
      "text": "So I define trust a little differently."
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 275800.0,
      "end_time": 281240.0,
      "text": "I define trust as a confident relationship to the unknown."
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 281920.0,
      "end_time": 284160.0,
      "text": "Now, when you view trust through this lens,"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 284400.0,
      "end_time": 287696.0,
      "text": "it starts to explain why it has the unique capacity"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 287720.0,
      "end_time": 290816.0,
      "text": "to enable us to cope with uncertainty,"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 290840.0,
      "end_time": 293856.0,
      "text": "to place our faith in strangers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 293880.0,
      "end_time": 295760.0,
      "text": "to keep moving forward."
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 296400.0,
      "end_time": 299176.0,
      "text": "Human beings are remarkable"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 299200.0,
      "end_time": 300880.0,
      "text": "at taking trust leaps."
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 301400.0,
      "end_time": 304376.0,
      "text": "Do you remember the first time you put your credit card details"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 304400.0,
      "end_time": 305616.0,
      "text": "into a website?"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 305640.0,
      "end_time": 306976.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s a trust leap."
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 307000.0,
      "end_time": 309936.0,
      "text": "I distinctly remember telling my dad"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 309960.0,
      "end_time": 315216.0,
      "text": "that I wanted to buy a navy blue secondhand Peugeot on eBay,"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 315240.0,
      "end_time": 316896.0,
      "text": "and he rightfully pointed out"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 316920.0,
      "end_time": 319296.0,
      "text": "that the seller&#39;s name was \"Invisible Wizard\""
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 319320.0,
      "end_time": 322416.0,
      "text": "and that this probably was not such a good idea."
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 322440.0,
      "end_time": 324136.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 324160.0,
      "end_time": 327576.0,
      "text": "So my work, my research focuses on how technology"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 327600.0,
      "end_time": 330256.0,
      "text": "is transforming the social glue of society,"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 330280.0,
      "end_time": 331936.0,
      "text": "trust between people,"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 331960.0,
      "end_time": 334215.0,
      "text": "and it&#39;s a fascinating area to study,"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 334240.0,
      "end_time": 337616.0,
      "text": "because there&#39;s still so much we do not know."
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 337640.0,
      "end_time": 342736.0,
      "text": "For instance, do men and women trust differently in digital environments?"
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 342760.0,
      "end_time": 347656.0,
      "text": "Does the way we build trust face-to-face translate online?"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 347680.0,
      "end_time": 349616.0,
      "text": "Does trust transfer?"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 349640.0,
      "end_time": 352336.0,
      "text": "So if you trust finding a mate on Tinder,"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 352360.0,
      "end_time": 355720.0,
      "text": "are you more likely to trust finding a ride on BlaBlaCar?"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 356440.0,
      "end_time": 359695.0,
      "text": "But from studying hundreds of networks and marketplaces,"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 359720.0,
      "end_time": 362536.0,
      "text": "there is a common pattern that people follow,"
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 362560.0,
      "end_time": 365216.0,
      "text": "and I call it \"climbing the trust stack.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 365240.0,
      "end_time": 368440.0,
      "text": "Let me use BlaBlaCar as an example to bring it to life."
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 369800.0,
      "end_time": 370376.0,
      "text": "On the first level,"
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 370400.0,
      "end_time": 372575.0,
      "text": "you have to trust the idea."
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 372600.0,
      "end_time": 373816.0,
      "text": "So you have to trust"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 373840.0,
      "end_time": 377239.0,
      "text": "the idea of ride-sharing is safe and worth trying."
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 377640.0,
      "end_time": 382336.0,
      "text": "The second level is about having confidence in the platform,"
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 382360.0,
      "end_time": 386496.0,
      "text": "that BlaBlaCar will help you if something goes wrong."
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 386520.0,
      "end_time": 390176.0,
      "text": "And the third level is about using little bits of information"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 390200.0,
      "end_time": 393680.0,
      "text": "to decide whether the other person is trustworthy."
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 394200.0,
      "end_time": 396816.0,
      "text": "Now, the first time we climb the trust stack,"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 396840.0,
      "end_time": 400950.0,
      "text": "it feels weird, even risky,"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 400120.0,
      "end_time": 405960.0,
      "text": "but we get to a point where these ideas seem totally normal."
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 405120.0,
      "end_time": 407416.0,
      "text": "Our behaviors transform,"
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 407440.0,
      "end_time": 409416.0,
      "text": "often relatively quickly."
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 409440.0,
      "end_time": 414240.0,
      "text": "In other words, trust enables change and innovation."
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 415280.0,
      "end_time": 418695.0,
      "text": "So an idea that intrigued me, and I&#39;d like you to consider,"
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 418720.0,
      "end_time": 421256.0,
      "text": "is whether we can better understand"
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 421280.0,
      "end_time": 425455.0,
      "text": "major waves of disruption and change in individuals in society"
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 425480.0,
      "end_time": 427536.0,
      "text": "through the lens of trust."
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 427560.0,
      "end_time": 430856.0,
      "text": "Well, it turns out that trust has only evolved"
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 430880.0,
      "end_time": 435536.0,
      "text": "in three significant chapters throughout the course of human history:"
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 435560.0,
      "end_time": 437776.0,
      "text": "local, institutional"
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 437800.0,
      "end_time": 440200.0,
      "text": "and what we&#39;re now entering, distributed."
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 440680.0,
      "end_time": 443160.0,
      "text": "So for a long time,"
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 443400.0,
      "end_time": 444296.0,
      "text": "until the mid-1800s,"
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 444320.0,
      "end_time": 448256.0,
      "text": "trust was built around tight-knit relationships."
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 448280.0,
      "end_time": 450296.0,
      "text": "So say I lived in a village"
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 450320.0,
      "end_time": 452896.0,
      "text": "with the first five rows of this audience,"
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 452920.0,
      "end_time": 454856.0,
      "text": "and we all knew one another,"
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 454880.0,
      "end_time": 457776.0,
      "text": "and say I wanted to borrow money."
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 457800.0,
      "end_time": 460776.0,
      "text": "The man who had his eyes wide open, he might lend it to me,"
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 460800.0,
      "end_time": 462896.0,
      "text": "and if I didn&#39;t pay him back,"
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 462920.0,
      "end_time": 464576.0,
      "text": "you&#39;d all know I was dodgy."
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 464600.0,
      "end_time": 466256.0,
      "text": "I would get a bad reputation,"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 466280.0,
      "end_time": 469335.0,
      "text": "and you would refuse to do business with me in the future."
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 469360.0,
      "end_time": 473576.0,
      "text": "Trust was mostly local and accountability-based."
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 473600.0,
      "end_time": 474936.0,
      "text": "In the mid-19th century,"
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 474960.0,
      "end_time": 478376.0,
      "text": "society went through a tremendous amount of change."
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 478400.0,
      "end_time": 482176.0,
      "text": "People moved to fast-growing cities such as London and San Francisco,"
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 482200.0,
      "end_time": 487560.0,
      "text": "and a local banker here was replaced by large corporations"
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 487800.0,
      "end_time": 489976.0,
      "text": "that didn&#39;t know us as individuals."
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 490000.0,
      "end_time": 491976.0,
      "text": "We started to place our trust"
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 492000.0,
      "end_time": 495576.0,
      "text": "into black box systems of authority,"
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 495600.0,
      "end_time": 499896.0,
      "text": "things like legal contracts and regulation and insurance,"
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 499920.0,
      "end_time": 503936.0,
      "text": "and less trust directly in other people."
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 503960.0,
      "end_time": 507816.0,
      "text": "Trust became institutional and commission-based."
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 507840.0,
      "end_time": 512655.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s widely talked about how trust in institutions and many corporate brands"
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 512679.0,
      "end_time": 516415.0,
      "text": "has been steadily declining and continues to do so."
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 516440.00000000006,
      "end_time": 522560.00000000006,
      "text": "I am constantly stunned by major breaches of trust:"
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 522799.99999999994,
      "end_time": 524576.0,
      "text": "the News Corp phone hacking,"
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 524600.0,
      "end_time": 527416.0,
      "text": "the Volkswagen emissions scandal,"
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 527440.0,
      "end_time": 530775.0,
      "text": "the widespread abuse in the Catholic Church,"
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 530799.0,
      "end_time": 534150.0,
      "text": "the fact that only one measly banker"
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 534390.0,
      "end_time": 537336.0,
      "text": "went to jail after the great financial crisis,"
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 537360.0,
      "end_time": 539416.0,
      "text": "or more recently the Panama Papers"
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 539440.0,
      "end_time": 544576.0,
      "text": "that revealed how the rich can exploit offshore tax regimes."
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 544600.0,
      "end_time": 547560.0,
      "text": "And the thing that really surprises me"
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 547800.0,
      "end_time": 551960.0,
      "text": "is why do leaders find it so hard"
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 551120.0,
      "end_time": 554296.0,
      "text": "to apologize, I mean sincerely apologize,"
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 554320.0,
      "end_time": 556480.0,
      "text": "when our trust is broken?"
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 557360.0,
      "end_time": 561496.0,
      "text": "It would be easy to conclude that institutional trust isn&#39;t working"
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 561520.0,
      "end_time": 563160.0,
      "text": "because we are fed up"
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 563400.0,
      "end_time": 565935.0,
      "text": "with the sheer audacity of dishonest elites,"
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 565960.0,
      "end_time": 567936.0,
      "text": "but what&#39;s happening now"
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 567960.0,
      "end_time": 573576.0,
      "text": "runs deeper than the rampant questioning of the size and structure of institutions."
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 573600.0,
      "end_time": 575616.0,
      "text": "We&#39;re starting to realize"
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 575640.0,
      "end_time": 577415.0,
      "text": "that institutional trust"
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 577440.0,
      "end_time": 580416.0,
      "text": "wasn&#39;t designed for the digital age."
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 580440.0,
      "end_time": 584960.0,
      "text": "Conventions of how trust is built,"
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 584120.0,
      "end_time": 586456.0,
      "text": "managed, lost and repaired --"
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 586480.0,
      "end_time": 588976.0,
      "text": "in brands, leaders and entire systems --"
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 589000.0,
      "end_time": 591000.0,
      "text": "is being turned upside down."
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 591760.0,
      "end_time": 593856.0,
      "text": "Now, this is exciting,"
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 593880.0,
      "end_time": 595415.0,
      "text": "but it&#39;s frightening,"
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 595440.0,
      "end_time": 598136.0,
      "text": "because it forces many of us to have to rethink"
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 598160.0,
      "end_time": 602856.0,
      "text": "how trust is built and destroyed with our customers, with our employees,"
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 602880.0,
      "end_time": 604360.0,
      "text": "even our loved ones."
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 605800.0,
      "end_time": 611976.0,
      "text": "The other day, I was talking to the CEO of a leading international hotel brand,"
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 612000.0,
      "end_time": 615240.0,
      "text": "and as is often the case, we got onto the topic of Airbnb."
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 615840.0,
      "end_time": 620936.0,
      "text": "And he admitted to me that he was perplexed by their success."
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 620960.0,
      "end_time": 623960.0,
      "text": "He was perplexed at how a company"
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 623120.0,
      "end_time": 627296.0,
      "text": "that depends on the willingness of strangers to trust one another"
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 627320.0,
      "end_time": 631280.0,
      "text": "could work so well across 191 countries."
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 631920.0,
      "end_time": 635550.0,
      "text": "So I said to him that I had a confession to make,"
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 635800.0,
      "end_time": 637560.0,
      "text": "and he looked at me a bit strangely,"
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 637800.0,
      "end_time": 638456.0,
      "text": "and I said --"
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 638480.0,
      "end_time": 640496.0,
      "text": "and I&#39;m sure many of you do this as well --"
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 640520.0,
      "end_time": 643160.0,
      "text": "I don&#39;t always bother to hang my towels up"
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 643400.0,
      "end_time": 645976.0,
      "text": "when I&#39;m finished in the hotel,"
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 646000.0,
      "end_time": 648640.0,
      "text": "but I would never do this as a guest on Airbnb."
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 649560.0,
      "end_time": 652896.0,
      "text": "And the reason why I would never do this as a guest on Airbnb"
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 652920.0,
      "end_time": 656575.0,
      "text": "is because guests know that they&#39;ll be rated by hosts,"
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 656600.0,
      "end_time": 660336.0,
      "text": "and that those ratings are likely to impact their ability"
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 660360.0,
      "end_time": 662400.0,
      "text": "to transact in the future."
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 662680.0,
      "end_time": 666896.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s a simple illustration of how online trust will change our behaviors"
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 666920.0,
      "end_time": 668216.0,
      "text": "in the real world,"
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 668240.0,
      "end_time": 670736.0,
      "text": "make us more accountable"
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 670760.0,
      "end_time": 674200.0,
      "text": "in ways we cannot yet even imagine."
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 674880.0,
      "end_time": 677936.0,
      "text": "I am not saying we do not need hotels"
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 677960.0,
      "end_time": 680296.0,
      "text": "or traditional forms of authority."
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 680320.0,
      "end_time": 682416.0,
      "text": "But what we cannot deny"
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 682440.0,
      "end_time": 686696.0,
      "text": "is that the way trust flows through society is changing,"
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 686720.0,
      "end_time": 689160.0,
      "text": "and it&#39;s creating this big shift"
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 689400.0,
      "end_time": 690896.0,
      "text": "away from the 20th century"
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 690920.0,
      "end_time": 693736.0,
      "text": "that was defined by institutional trust"
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 693760.0,
      "end_time": 696256.0,
      "text": "towards the 21st century"
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 696280.0,
      "end_time": 698920.0,
      "text": "that will be fueled by distributed trust."
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 699480.0,
      "end_time": 703656.0,
      "text": "Trust is no longer top-down."
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 703680.0,
      "end_time": 705776.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s being unbundled and inverted."
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 705800.0,
      "end_time": 708640.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s no longer opaque and linear."
    },
    {
      "index": 229,
      "start_time": 709160.0,
      "end_time": 712136.0,
      "text": "A new recipe for trust is emerging"
    },
    {
      "index": 230,
      "start_time": 712160.0,
      "end_time": 716550.0,
      "text": "that once again is distributed amongst people"
    },
    {
      "index": 231,
      "start_time": 716800.0,
      "end_time": 718216.0,
      "text": "and is accountability-based."
    },
    {
      "index": 232,
      "start_time": 718240.0,
      "end_time": 721656.0,
      "text": "And this shift is only going to accelerate"
    },
    {
      "index": 233,
      "start_time": 721680.0,
      "end_time": 724415.0,
      "text": "with the emergence of the blockchain,"
    },
    {
      "index": 234,
      "start_time": 724440.0,
      "end_time": 728800.0,
      "text": "the innovative ledger technology underpinning Bitcoin."
    },
    {
      "index": 235,
      "start_time": 728800.0,
      "end_time": 731736.0,
      "text": "Now let&#39;s be honest,"
    },
    {
      "index": 236,
      "start_time": 731760.0,
      "end_time": 735216.0,
      "text": "getting our heads around the way blockchain works"
    },
    {
      "index": 237,
      "start_time": 735240.0,
      "end_time": 736680.0,
      "text": "is mind-blowing."
    },
    {
      "index": 238,
      "start_time": 737720.0,
      "end_time": 740976.0,
      "text": "And one of the reasons why is it involves processing"
    },
    {
      "index": 239,
      "start_time": 741000.0,
      "end_time": 743656.0,
      "text": "some pretty complicated concepts"
    },
    {
      "index": 240,
      "start_time": 743680.0,
      "end_time": 745175.0,
      "text": "with terrible names."
    },
    {
      "index": 241,
      "start_time": 745200.0,
      "end_time": 749696.0,
      "text": "I mean, cryptographic algorithms and hash functions,"
    },
    {
      "index": 242,
      "start_time": 749720.0,
      "end_time": 752776.0,
      "text": "and people called miners, who verify transactions --"
    },
    {
      "index": 243,
      "start_time": 752800.0,
      "end_time": 756376.0,
      "text": "all that was created by this mysterious person"
    },
    {
      "index": 244,
      "start_time": 756400.0,
      "end_time": 759136.0,
      "text": "or persons called Satoshi Nakamoto."
    },
    {
      "index": 245,
      "start_time": 759160.0,
      "end_time": 764815.0,
      "text": "Now, that is a massive trust leap that hasn&#39;t happened yet."
    },
    {
      "index": 246,
      "start_time": 764840.0,
      "end_time": 767896.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 247,
      "start_time": 767920.0,
      "end_time": 769376.0,
      "text": "But let&#39;s try to imagine this."
    },
    {
      "index": 248,
      "start_time": 769400.0,
      "end_time": 773960.0,
      "text": "So \"The Economist\" eloquently described the blockchain"
    },
    {
      "index": 249,
      "start_time": 773120.0,
      "end_time": 776776.0,
      "text": "as the great chain of being sure about things."
    },
    {
      "index": 250,
      "start_time": 776800.0,
      "end_time": 781856.0,
      "text": "The easiest way I can describe it is imagine the blocks as spreadsheets,"
    },
    {
      "index": 251,
      "start_time": 781880.0,
      "end_time": 784856.0,
      "text": "and they are filled with assets."
    },
    {
      "index": 252,
      "start_time": 784880.0,
      "end_time": 787296.0,
      "text": "So that could be a property title."
    },
    {
      "index": 253,
      "start_time": 787320.0,
      "end_time": 789336.0,
      "text": "It could be a stock trade."
    },
    {
      "index": 254,
      "start_time": 789360.0,
      "end_time": 792320.0,
      "text": "It could be a creative asset, such as the rights to a song."
    },
    {
      "index": 255,
      "start_time": 792960.0,
      "end_time": 795976.0,
      "text": "Every time something moves"
    },
    {
      "index": 256,
      "start_time": 796000.0,
      "end_time": 799816.0,
      "text": "from one place on the register to somewhere else,"
    },
    {
      "index": 257,
      "start_time": 799840.0,
      "end_time": 802936.0,
      "text": "that asset transfer is time-stamped"
    },
    {
      "index": 258,
      "start_time": 802960.0,
      "end_time": 806376.0,
      "text": "and publicly recorded on the blockchain."
    },
    {
      "index": 259,
      "start_time": 806400.0,
      "end_time": 808280.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s that simple. Right."
    },
    {
      "index": 260,
      "start_time": 808720.0,
      "end_time": 811816.0,
      "text": "So the real implication of the blockchain"
    },
    {
      "index": 261,
      "start_time": 811840.0,
      "end_time": 815976.0,
      "text": "is that it removes the need for any kind of third party,"
    },
    {
      "index": 262,
      "start_time": 816000.0,
      "end_time": 817336.0,
      "text": "such as a lawyer,"
    },
    {
      "index": 263,
      "start_time": 817360.0,
      "end_time": 820816.0,
      "text": "or a trusted intermediary, or maybe not a government intermediary"
    },
    {
      "index": 264,
      "start_time": 820840.0,
      "end_time": 822656.0,
      "text": "to facilitate the exchange."
    },
    {
      "index": 265,
      "start_time": 822680.0,
      "end_time": 824935.0,
      "text": "So if we go back to the trust stack,"
    },
    {
      "index": 266,
      "start_time": 824960.0,
      "end_time": 827696.0,
      "text": "you still have to trust the idea,"
    },
    {
      "index": 267,
      "start_time": 827720.0,
      "end_time": 830160.0,
      "text": "you have to trust the platform,"
    },
    {
      "index": 268,
      "start_time": 830400.0,
      "end_time": 832976.0,
      "text": "but you don&#39;t have to trust the other person"
    },
    {
      "index": 269,
      "start_time": 833000.0,
      "end_time": 834936.0,
      "text": "in the traditional sense."
    },
    {
      "index": 270,
      "start_time": 834960.0,
      "end_time": 837456.0,
      "text": "The implications are huge."
    },
    {
      "index": 271,
      "start_time": 837480.0,
      "end_time": 841176.0,
      "text": "In the same way the internet blew open the doors to an age of information"
    },
    {
      "index": 272,
      "start_time": 841200.0,
      "end_time": 842616.0,
      "text": "available to everyone,"
    },
    {
      "index": 273,
      "start_time": 842640.0,
      "end_time": 846960.0,
      "text": "the blockchain will revolutionize trust on a global scale."
    },
    {
      "index": 274,
      "start_time": 848240.0,
      "end_time": 852176.0,
      "text": "Now, I&#39;ve waited to the end intentionally to mention Uber,"
    },
    {
      "index": 275,
      "start_time": 852200.0,
      "end_time": 855656.0,
      "text": "because I recognize that it is a contentious"
    },
    {
      "index": 276,
      "start_time": 855680.0,
      "end_time": 858295.0,
      "text": "and widely overused example,"
    },
    {
      "index": 277,
      "start_time": 858320.0,
      "end_time": 861560.0,
      "text": "but in the context of a new era of trust, it&#39;s a great case study."
    },
    {
      "index": 278,
      "start_time": 861920.0,
      "end_time": 866656.0,
      "text": "Now, we will see cases of abuse of distributed trust."
    },
    {
      "index": 279,
      "start_time": 866680.0,
      "end_time": 870335.0,
      "text": "We&#39;ve already seen this, and it can go horribly wrong."
    },
    {
      "index": 280,
      "start_time": 870360.0,
      "end_time": 875536.0,
      "text": "I am not surprised that we are seeing protests from taxi associations"
    },
    {
      "index": 281,
      "start_time": 875560.0,
      "end_time": 876896.0,
      "text": "all around the world"
    },
    {
      "index": 282,
      "start_time": 876920.0,
      "end_time": 881800.0,
      "text": "trying to get governments to ban Uber based on claims that it is unsafe."
    },
    {
      "index": 283,
      "start_time": 882320.0,
      "end_time": 886696.0,
      "text": "I happened to be in London the day that these protests took place,"
    },
    {
      "index": 284,
      "start_time": 886720.0,
      "end_time": 888696.0,
      "text": "and I happened to notice a tweet"
    },
    {
      "index": 285,
      "start_time": 888720.0,
      "end_time": 892336.0,
      "text": "from Matt Hancock, who is a British minister for business."
    },
    {
      "index": 286,
      "start_time": 892360.0,
      "end_time": 893576.0,
      "text": "And he wrote,"
    },
    {
      "index": 287,
      "start_time": 893600.0,
      "end_time": 897576.0,
      "text": "\"Does anyone have details of this #Uber app everyone&#39;s talking about?"
    },
    {
      "index": 288,
      "start_time": 897600.0,
      "end_time": 898800.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 289,
      "start_time": 899880.0,
      "end_time": 902520.0,
      "text": "I&#39;d never heard of it until today.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 290,
      "start_time": 903560.0,
      "end_time": 906839.0,
      "text": "Now, the taxi associations,"
    },
    {
      "index": 291,
      "start_time": 907800.0,
      "end_time": 910536.0,
      "text": "they legitimized the first layer of the trust stack."
    },
    {
      "index": 292,
      "start_time": 910560.0,
      "end_time": 913896.0,
      "text": "They legitimized the idea that they were trying to eliminate,"
    },
    {
      "index": 293,
      "start_time": 913920.0,
      "end_time": 919550.0,
      "text": "and sign-ups increased by 850 percent in 24 hours."
    },
    {
      "index": 294,
      "start_time": 919800.0,
      "end_time": 922336.0,
      "text": "Now, this is a really strong illustration"
    },
    {
      "index": 295,
      "start_time": 922360.0,
      "end_time": 928176.0,
      "text": "of how once a trust shift has happened around a behavior or an entire sector,"
    },
    {
      "index": 296,
      "start_time": 928200.0,
      "end_time": 930440.0,
      "text": "you cannot reverse the story."
    },
    {
      "index": 297,
      "start_time": 931120.0,
      "end_time": 934976.0,
      "text": "Every day, five million people will take a trust leap"
    },
    {
      "index": 298,
      "start_time": 935000.0,
      "end_time": 936536.0,
      "text": "and ride with Uber."
    },
    {
      "index": 299,
      "start_time": 936560.0,
      "end_time": 939776.0,
      "text": "In China, on Didi, the ride-sharing platform,"
    },
    {
      "index": 300,
      "start_time": 939800.0,
      "end_time": 942695.0,
      "text": "11 million rides taken every day."
    },
    {
      "index": 301,
      "start_time": 942720.0,
      "end_time": 946336.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s 127 rides per second,"
    },
    {
      "index": 302,
      "start_time": 946360.0,
      "end_time": 949176.0,
      "text": "showing that this is a cross-cultural phenomenon."
    },
    {
      "index": 303,
      "start_time": 949200.0,
      "end_time": 953376.0,
      "text": "And the fascinating thing is that both drivers and passengers report"
    },
    {
      "index": 304,
      "start_time": 953400.0,
      "end_time": 955896.0,
      "text": "that seeing a name"
    },
    {
      "index": 305,
      "start_time": 955920.0,
      "end_time": 958896.0,
      "text": "and seeing someone&#39;s photo and their rating"
    },
    {
      "index": 306,
      "start_time": 958920.0,
      "end_time": 961175.0,
      "text": "makes them feel safer,"
    },
    {
      "index": 307,
      "start_time": 961200.0,
      "end_time": 962776.0,
      "text": "and as you may have experienced,"
    },
    {
      "index": 308,
      "start_time": 962800.0,
      "end_time": 966760.0,
      "text": "even behave a little more nicely in the taxi cab."
    },
    {
      "index": 309,
      "start_time": 967360.0,
      "end_time": 971560.0,
      "text": "Uber and Didi are early but powerful examples"
    },
    {
      "index": 310,
      "start_time": 971800.0,
      "end_time": 975560.0,
      "text": "of how technology is creating trust between people"
    },
    {
      "index": 311,
      "start_time": 975800.0,
      "end_time": 978360.0,
      "text": "in ways and on a scale never possible before."
    },
    {
      "index": 312,
      "start_time": 979120.0,
      "end_time": 985176.0,
      "text": "Today, many of us are comfortable getting into cars driven by strangers."
    },
    {
      "index": 313,
      "start_time": 985200.0,
      "end_time": 989496.0,
      "text": "We meet up with someone we swiped right to be matched with."
    },
    {
      "index": 314,
      "start_time": 989520.0,
      "end_time": 993456.0,
      "text": "We share our homes with people we do not know."
    },
    {
      "index": 315,
      "start_time": 993480.0,
      "end_time": 995840.0,
      "text": "This is just the beginning,"
    },
    {
      "index": 316,
      "start_time": 996440.0,
      "end_time": 999160.0,
      "text": "because the real disruption happening"
    },
    {
      "index": 317,
      "start_time": 999400.0,
      "end_time": 1000976.0,
      "text": "isn&#39;t technological."
    },
    {
      "index": 318,
      "start_time": 1001000.0,
      "end_time": 1003320.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s the trust shift it creates,"
    },
    {
      "index": 319,
      "start_time": 1003880.0,
      "end_time": 1008976.0,
      "text": "and for my part, I want to help people understand this new era of trust"
    },
    {
      "index": 320,
      "start_time": 1009000.0,
      "end_time": 1010656.0,
      "text": "so that we can get it right"
    },
    {
      "index": 321,
      "start_time": 1010680.0,
      "end_time": 1014575.0,
      "text": "and we can embrace the opportunities to redesign systems"
    },
    {
      "index": 322,
      "start_time": 1014600.0,
      "end_time": 1018696.0,
      "text": "that are more transparent, inclusive and accountable."
    },
    {
      "index": 323,
      "start_time": 1018720.0,
      "end_time": 1019976.0,
      "text": "Thank you very much."
    },
    {
      "index": 324,
      "start_time": 1020000.0,
      "end_time": 1022576.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 325,
      "start_time": 1022600.0,
      "end_time": 1023816.0,
      "text": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 326,
      "start_time": 1023840.0,
      "end_time": 1027548.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}